{"type":"message","id":"273965ac","parentId":"91daad45","timestamp":"2026-03-30T13:33:31.930Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand both errors:\n\n1. **旅游攻略推送** (aa7a03fc): The cron job's delivery target is configured but the isolated session can't auto-detect the Feishu chat context. The delivery configuration has `target: \"user:ou_e48f6c4c0395f45b74b51525f348678b\"` which is correct. But the error says \"Delivering to Feishu requires target <chatId|user:openId|chat:chatId>\" - this seems like the target is already set correctly as `user:ou_e48f6c4c0395f45b74b51525f348678b`. \n\nThe issue might be that when the cron job runs, the isolated session doesn't have the inbound context from the original conversation, so even though the target is specified in the delivery config, the Feishu plugin might not be using it correctly for the announcement. The jobs.json delivery.target is already set to \"user:ou_e48f6c4c0395f45b74b51525f348678b\", but the error persists, which suggests the announce delivery mode might not be properly resolving the target when the cron job fires.\n\nLooking at the second error for ed08c32f, it also shows \"Delivering to Feishu requires target\" even though the target is already configured, which points to the same underlying issue with how the delivery mode is handling the target specification. So the Feishu delivery error is the same across both jobs - the isolated cron session can't infer the chat context and needs the target specified. The ctrip_tracker script itself ran fine, but the delivery failed because there's no chat context in that isolated session. I need to fix the Feishu delivery issue."},{"type":"text","text":"找到问题了，两个任务都是**飞书推送失败**——isolated session 跑 cron 时没有当前聊天上下文，导致 delivery 找不到目标。\n\n**当前状态：**\n- ✈️ 机票日报：脚本跑成功了，但飞书推送失败\n- 🌍 旅游攻略：只获取到1条内容，飞书推送也失败\n\n**根本原因：** delivery 里的 target 是 `user:ou_e48f6c4c0395f45b74b51525f348678b`，但 isolated session 投递时可能不认这个格式。\n\n要我修复这两个 cron job